reviewText: If you're a fan of Irish History, you'll love this...just be prepared to be punched in the gut at the end. A very "Irish" ending.
What an amazing movie. And the ending. Don't even see it coming. So beautifully done. I definitely plan on visiting this place on my next trip to Ireland. <3
fast service & great documentry

Great documentary about Glasnevin that really leaves you thinking about how much history has passed through the gates of the cemetery. It is so well narrated throughout and I was not expecting the conclusion when it came. Well worth watching, I highly recommend it.
Really interesting!  Must watch to the end.
This is an interesting documentary that turns into a heartbreaking personal story. I found it very moving.
One of the best movies I have seen this year.
Excellent documentary on a portrait of Irish History and the significance of the work today.
this was fantastic! must see for all....
great movie
This was a great dvd.  It was very informative and interesting.
Respectful, thoughtful, reflective documentary.
Very interesting and well made film
A beautiful film of a beautiful place.  Don't let the fact that this is a film about a cemetery hold you back from watching it.

I absolutely loved it. Beautifully filmed, very sensitively handled and emotionally powerful. The history and characters were fascinating and the story of the people was incredible. The cinema was absolutely silent at the end
Excellent film, my wife and I thoroughly enjoyed it.
We visited this cemetery this year, I wish we would have seen this first
I really enjoyed this documentary. It was very informative and the ending is particularly heart wrenching.
A very interesting documentary, and a heartbreaking ending.
Good documentary with a surprise ending. Really enjoyed it
Very moving documentary

...and when your done with Rebel Rosa and 1916 Irish Rebellion,  youll know all the relevant names. Then watch One  Million Dubliners. You will laugh, you will learn, you might feel like you met a friend but for the end, if you have a heart, you will cry!
Death leaves a heartache no one can heal; Love leaves a memory no one can steal ...  Proud of my Irish roots, this was beautiful.
Truly an Irish story.
Warm, funny, sad, and very human.
Tears. . .
So moving. I am still thinking about it a week after watching.
Wow! What a documentary. It wasn't exactly what I was expecting, but very interesting, and then ending...so surprising!
Really a great documentary.  Will stay with you for days.
Incredible look at the Dublin cenetry. Very informative.
